Package src

Interface BinaryTreeInterface<T>

All Superinterfaces:
TreeInterface<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BinaryTree
public interface BinaryTreeInterface<T> extends TreeInterface<T>
This is the BinaryTreeInterface which extends the TreeInterface - a separately documented interface. The BinaryTreeInterface introduces two additional methods: setRootData and setTree. While all trees have a height, nodes, the state of being empty, and the functionality of being cleared, a Binary tree has the property of having a maximum of two subtrees. The two methods are documented separately.
Version:
1.0
Author:
George Matta, Matt Dong
